Tsuyoshi CHO 1日 20:53:54 Slack
直した
不明な関数もあるだろうけど、ニュアンスで
[[ダウンロード: .nyagos(Lua)]] 
-- prompt
nyagos.prompt = function(this)
  -- path,title,prompt
  local path = getCompressedPath(3):gsub('\\', '/')
  local title = path .. " - NYAGOS"
  local admin = nyagos.elevated()
  if admin then
    title = title .. "(admin)"
  end

  local prompt = ''
  if nyagos.which("starship") then
    prompt = prompt .. nyagos.eval('starship prompt 2> nul') .. ' '
  else
    local pathBlock = ''
    if admin then
      pathBlock = '$e[30;40;1m[$e[40;31;1m'..path..'$e[30;40;1m]$e[37;1m'
    else
      pathBlock = '$e[30;40;1m[$e[40;36;1m'..path..'$e[30;40;1m]$e[37;1m'
    end
    prompt = prompt .. makePrompt(pathBlock)
  end

  return nyagos.default_prompt(prompt,title)
end

[[ダウンロード: .gitconfig.alias(Shell)]] 
	sw = "!f () {\
		checkouted=0;\
		if [ \"${#}\" -eq 1 -a \"${1}\" = \"-\" ]; then\
			git switch -;\
			checkouted=1;\
		elif [ \"${#}\" -eq 1 ]; then\
			match_num=$(git branch | sed 's/^..//' | grep -x \"${*}\" | wc -l);\
			if [ 1 -eq \"${match_num}\" ]; then\
				git switch ${*};\
				checkouted=1;\
			fi;\
		fi;\
		if [ 1 -eq \"${checkouted}\" ]; then\
			:;\
		elif which fzf >/dev/null 2>&1; then\
			git branch --sort=authordate | fzf  --header='local-branch' --prompt='switch\\> ' --query=\"${*}\" --select-1 | tr -d ' \\*' | xargs -r -n 1 git switch;\
		elif which peco >/dev/null 2>&1; then\
			git branch --sort=authordate | peco                         --prompt='switch\\> ' --query=\"${*}\" --select-1 | tr -d ' \\*' | xargs -r -n 1 git switch;\
		elif [ \"${#}\" -ge 1 ]; then\
			git switch ${*};\
		fi;\
	};f"

以下のようなかんじw
1. git の switchは cdライクに - で1つ前に戻る
2. ブランチに完全一致ならfzfにいかずにやる
3. ブランチに複数あるなら、クエリにセットしてfzf(/peco)、そこでfuzzy matchで1つなら即座に
4. それ以外のオプションは直に渡す(ただし動作未確認)

[[ダウンロード: fzf-gh-pr(Shell)]] 
FZF_GH_PR_EXTRA_ARG=${FZF_GH_PR_EXTRA_ARG:-''}
FZF_GH_PR_BINDKEY=${FZF_GH_PR_BINDKEY:-'^x^p^r'}

function fzf-gh-pr-selection() {
  local out pr key fzf_command command

  pr_list_command='gh pr list'
  fzf_command='fzf --query "$LBUFFER" --prompt="Pull Request> " --preview="gh pr view {1}" --expect=ctrl-o,ctrl-c'
  command="$pr_list_command | $fzf_command"

  IFS=$'\n' out=$(eval $command)
  key=$(echo "$out" | head -1)
  pr=$(echo "$out" | head -2 | tail -1 | awk '{ print $1 }')

  if [[ $pr != "" ]]; then
    if [[ $key == "ctrl-o" ]]; then
      eval "gh pr view --web $pr"
    elif [[ $key == "ctrl-c" ]]; then
      BUFFER="gh pr checkout $pr"
      CURSOR=$#BUFFER
    else
      eval "gh pr view $pr"
    fi
  fi
  zle reset-prompt
}
zle -N fzf-gh-pr-selection
bindkey $FZF_GH_PR_BINDKEY fzf-gh-pr-selection

ycino 15日 11:57:01 Slack 
   RELOAD INPUT
       reload(...)  action  is  used  to  dynamically update the input list without restarting fzf. It takes the same command template with placeholder expressions as exe-
       cute(...).

       See <https://github.com/junegunn/fzf/issues/1750> for more info.

       e.g.
            # Update the list of processes by pressing CTRL-R
            ps -ef | fzf --bind 'ctrl-r:reload(ps -ef)' --header 'Press CTRL-R to reload' \
                         --header-lines=1 --layout=reverse

            # Integration with ripgrep
            RG_PREFIX="rg --column --line-number --no-heading --color=always --smart-case "
            INITIAL_QUERY="foobar"
            FZF_DEFAULT_COMMAND="$RG_PREFIX '$INITIAL_QUERY'" \
              fzf --bind "change:reload:$RG_PREFIX {q} || true" \
                  --ansi --phony --query "$INITIAL_QUERY"

  function prompt_anyenv() {
    local ruby_version python_version node_version

    if which rbenv > /dev/null 2>&1; then
      ruby_version="Ruby-$(rbenv version-name)"
    fi
    if which pyenv > /dev/null 2>&1; then
      python_version="Python-$(pyenv version-name)"
    fi
    if which nodenv > /dev/null 2>&1; then
      node_version="Node-$(nodenv version-name)"
    fi
    p10k segment -f white -t "[%{$MAGENTA%}${ruby_version}%{$DEFAULT%} %{$GREEN%}${python_version}%{$DEFAULT%} %{$BLUE%}${node_version}%{$DEFAULT%}]"
  }

ycino 17日 00:14:42 Slack 
function fzf-direct-completion() {
  local tokens cmd lastcmd
  setopt localoptions noshwordsplit

  if [[ $BUFFER[-1] == $FZF_COMPLETION_TRIGGER && $BUFFER[-2] == " " ]]; then
    zle fzf-completion
    return
  fi

  if [[ $BUFFER[-1] != " " ]]; then
    zle expand-or-complete
    return
  fi

  tokens=(${(z)BUFFER})
  cmd=${tokens[1]}
  lastcmd=${tokens[-1]}

  if [[ $cmd == "git" ]]; then
    zle fzf-git-completion
  elif [[ $cmd == "rbenv" || $cmd == "pyenv" || $cmd == "nodenv" ]]; then
    zle fzf-anyenv-completion
  elif [[ $cmd == "tmux" ]]; then
    zle fzf-tmux-completion
  elif [[ $lastcmd == "rspec" || $lastcmd == "grspec" ]]; then
    zle fzf-rspec-completion
  else
    zle expand-or-complete
  fi
}
zle -N fzf-direct-completion
bindkey '^i'   fzf-direct-completion

Milly 17日 16:21:30
eval 使わずこう書けます
fzf_completion_foocommand=("echo bar qux")
command=foo

candidate_command="fzf_completion_${command}command"
# candidates=`${(Pz)candidate_command}`  # <= quote 考慮してなかった
candidates=`${(Q)${(z)${(P)candidate_command}}}`

echo $candidates
# => bar qux

fzf_completion_git_add_candidate=("git status --short")

eval '$'${candidate_command}
ycino 17日 16:17:36 Slack
あ、この書き方って配列になってるのか
さっきの拾いもののyamlパーサの仕様ですね
$ parse_yaml .zsh/fzf_completion_plugin/config/git.yml fzf_completion_
fzf_completion_git_add_command=("git add")
fzf_completion_git_add_candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_completion_git_add_fzf_options=("--multi --prompt 'Git Add Files>'")
fzf_completion_git_add_preview=("\"fzf-complete-git-preview {}\"")
fzf_completion_git_add_callback=("awk '{if (substr($0,2,1) !~ / /) print $2}'")
Milly 17日 16:21:30 Slack
eval 使わずこう書けます
fzf_completion_foocommand=("echo bar qux")
command=foo

candidate_command="fzf_completion_${command}command"
# candidates=`${(Pz)candidate_command}`  # <= quote 考慮してなかった
candidates=`${(Q)${(z)${(P)candidate_command}}}`

echo $candidates
# => bar qux

[[ダウンロード: fd(Shell)]] 
> fd -h
fd 8.0.0

USAGE:
    fd [FLAGS/OPTIONS] [<pattern>] [<path>...]

FLAGS:
    -H, --hidden            Search hidden files and directories
    -I, --no-ignore         Do not respect .(git|fd)ignore files
    -s, --case-sensitive    Case-sensitive search (default: smart case)
    -i, --ignore-case       Case-insensitive search (default: smart case)
    -g, --glob              Glob-based search (default: regular expression)
    -a, --absolute-path     Show absolute instead of relative paths
    -l, --list-details      Use a long listing format with file metadata
    -L, --follow            Follow symbolic links
    -p, --full-path         Search full path (default: file-/dirname only)
    -0, --print0            Separate results by the null character
    -h, --help              Prints help information
    -V, --version           Prints version information

OPTIONS:
    -d, --max-depth <depth>            Set maximum search depth (default: none)
    -t, --type <filetype>...
            Filter by type: file (f), directory (d), symlink (l),
            executable (x), empty (e), socket (s), pipe (p)
    -e, --extension <ext>...           Filter by file extension
    -x, --exec <cmd>                   Execute a command for each search result
    -X, --exec-batch <cmd>             Execute a command with all search results at once
    -E, --exclude <pattern>...         Exclude entries that match the given glob pattern
    -c, --color <when>                 When to use colors: never, *auto*, always
    -S, --size <size>...               Limit results based on the size of files.
        --changed-within <date|dur>    Filter by file modification time (newer than)
        --changed-before <date|dur>    Filter by file modification time (older than)

ARGS:
    <pattern>    the search pattern - a regular expression unless '--glob' is used
                 (optional)
    <path>...    the root directory for the filesystem search (optional)

Note: `fd -h` prints a short and concise overview while `fd --help` gives all details.

eval 使わずこう書けます
fzf_completion_foocommand=("echo bar qux")
command=foo

candidate_command="fzf_completion_${command}command"
# candidates=`${(Pz)candidate_command}`  # <= quote 考慮してなかった
candidates=`${(Q)${(z)${(P)candidate_command}}}`

echo $candidates
# => bar qux

ycino 20日 16:23:25 Slack 
setopt BASH_REMATCH

typeset -A array
array[(git checkout [a-zA-Z0-9]+ --)]="filename_completion"

for key in ${(k)array}; do
 [[ "git checkout abc --" =~ $key ]]
 if [[ $BASH_REMATCH[1] != "" ]]; then
   echo $BASH_REMATCH[1]
 fi
 unset BASH_REMATCH
done

ちなみにyamlの定義をやめて
$ parse_yaml config/git.yml fzf_preview_
fzf_preview_git_add_symbol=("git_add")
fzf_preview_git_add_candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_preview_git_add_fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Add Files> '")
fzf_preview_git_add_preview=("$FZF_PREVIEW_BIN_PATH/git-diff-preview {}")
fzf_preview_git_add_callback=("awk '{if (substr(\$0,2,1) !~ / /) print \$2}'")
fzf_preview_git_branch_symbol=("git_branch")
fzf_preview_git_branch_candidate=("git for-each-ref refs/heads refs/remotes --format='[branch] %(refname:short)' 2> /dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_branch_fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Branch> '")
fzf_preview_git_branch_preview=("git log \$(echo {} | awk '{ print \$2 }') --graph --color=always 2>/dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_branch_callback=("awk '{ print \$2 }'")
fzf_preview_git_reset_file_symbol=("git_reset_file")
fzf_preview_git_reset_file_candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_preview_git_reset_file_fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Reset Files> '")
fzf_preview_git_reset_file_preview=("$FZF_PREVIEW_BIN_PATH/git-diff-preview {}")
fzf_preview_git_reset_file_callback=("awk '{if (substr(\$0,1,1) ~ /M|A|D/) print \$2}'")
fzf_preview_git_reset_branch_symbol=("git_reset")
fzf_preview_git_reset_branch_candidate=("git for-each-ref refs/heads refs/remotes --format='[branch] %(refname:short)' 2> /dev/null && git for-each-ref refs/tags --format='[tag] %(refname:short)' --sort=-version:refname 2> /dev/null && git log --format='[commit] %h %s' 2> /dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_reset_branch_fzf_options=("--no-sort --ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Reset Branch> '")
fzf_preview_git_reset_branch_preview=("git show --color=always \$(echo {} | awk '{ print \$2 }') 2>/dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_reset_branch_callback=("awk '{ print \$2 }'")
fzf_preview_git_diff_file_symbol=("git_diff_file")
fzf_preview_git_diff_file_candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_preview_git_diff_file_fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Diff Files> '")
fzf_preview_git_diff_file_preview=("$FZF_PREVIEW_BIN_PATH/git-diff-preview {}")
fzf_preview_git_diff_file_callback=("awk '{ print \$2 }'")
fzf_preview_git_diff_branch_symbol=("git_diff_file")
fzf_preview_git_diff_branch_candidate=("git for-each-ref refs/heads refs/remotes --format='[branch] %(refname:short)' 2> /dev/null && git for-each-ref refs/tags --format='[tag] %(refname:short)' --sort=-version:refname 2> /dev/null && git log --format='[commit] %h %s' 2> /dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_diff_branch_fzf_options=("--no-sort --ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Diff Branch> '")
fzf_preview_git_diff_branch_preview=("git diff --color=always {2}")
fzf_preview_git_diff_branch_callback=("awk '{ print \$2 }'")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_file_symbol=("git_checkout_file")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_file_candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_file_fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Checkout Files> '")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_file_preview=("$FZF_PREVIEW_BIN_PATH/git-diff-preview {}")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_file_callback=("awk '{if (substr(\$0,1,1) ~ /M|A|D/) print \$2}'")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_branch_symbol=("git_checkout_branch")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_branch_candidate=("git for-each-ref refs/heads refs/remotes --format='[branch] %(refname:short)' 2> /dev/null && git for-each-ref refs/tags --format='[tag] %(refname:short)' --sort=-version:refname 2> /dev/null && git log --format='[commit] %h %s' 2> /dev/null")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_branch_fzf_options=("--no-sort --ansi --multi --prompt \"Git Checkout> \"")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_branch_preview=("([[ '{1}' == '[branch]' ]] && git log {2} --pretty='format:%C(yellow)%h %C(green)%cd %C(reset)%s %C(red)%d %C(cyan)[%an]' --date=iso --graph --color=always) || ([[ '{1}' == '[commit]' ]] && git show --color=always {2})")
fzf_preview_git_checkout_branch_callback=("awk '{ print \$2 }'")

ycino 20日 20:37:13 Slack
[[ダウンロード: 無題(Shell)]] 
typeset -g -A fzf_preview_commands=()

fzf_preview_commands[(gh issue view)]="gh_issue"
fzf_preview_commands[(gh issue view --web)]="gh_issue"

function gh_issue() {
  local id="gh_issue"

  local candidate_command="gh issue list --limit 100"

  local -a fzf_options
  fzf_options+=("--ansi")
  fzf_options+=("--height=100%")
  fzf_options+=("--prompt='Issue> '")
  fzf_options+=("--header='C-o: open, C-c: closed, C-a: all'")
  fzf_options+=('--preview="gh issue view {1}"')

  local -a bind=("${FZF_PREVIEW_DEFAULT_BIND}")
  bind+=("ctrl-o:reload(gh issue list --limit 100 --state open)")
  bind+=("ctrl-c:reload(gh issue list --limit 100 --state closed)")
  bind+=("ctrl-a:reload(gh issue list --limit 100 --state all)")
  fzf_options+=("--bind=\"${(j:,:)bind}\"")

  local callback=("awk '{ print \$1 }'")

  local complete_func_name="_fzf_complete_${id}"
  _create_complete_func $complete_func_name  "${callback}"
  FZF_COMPLETION_OPTS=${(j: :)${fzf_options}}
  eval $complete_func_name "\"${candidate_command}\""
}

Milly 20日 22:30:52 Slack
こんなファイル構成にして
+ config/
| + fzf-preview-git
| + fzf-preview-git_add
| +  :
| + fzf-preview-gh
| + fzf-preview-gh_issue
| +  :
+ src/
+ :

config の中身はこうして
# fzf-preview-git
symbols=(
  '(git add)'                     git_add
  '(git branch -[dD])'            git_branch
  '(git reset(| --(hard|soft)))'  git_reset_branch
)

# fzf-preview-git_add
candidate=("git status --short")
fzf_options=("--ansi --multi --prompt 'Git Add Files> '")
preview=("$FZF_PREVIEW_BIN_PATH/git-diff-preview {}")
callback=("awk '{if (substr(\$0,2,1) !~ / /) print \$2}'")

entry-point で autoload -Uz しておく
# fzf-preview.zsh
fpath+=${0:a:h}/config
for f in ${0:h}/config/*(N-.); autoload -Uz $f
unset f

参照するときにロードする
# src/completion.zsh
function _fzf-or-normal-completion() {
  local cmd='git'
  if typeset -f fzf-preview-${cmd} >/dev/null; then
    zle fzf-preview-completion $cmd
  else
    zle expand-or-complete
  fi
}
zle -N fzf-or-normal-completion _fzf-or-normal-completion

function _fzf-preview-completion() {
  local cmd=$1
  local cmdline='git add'
  local -A symbols
  fzf-preview-${cmd}
  local symbol=${symbols[(k)$cmdline]}
  if [[ -z $symbol ]]; then
    zle expand-or-complete
    return
  fi
  local candidate fzf_options preview callback
  fzf-preview-${symbol}
  print $candidate
  print $fzf_options
  print $preview
  print $callback
}
zle -N fzf-preview-completion _fzf-preview-completion

Milly 21日 11:32:41 Slack
autoload foo で foo function のスタブが作られます、中身は function foo { autoload -X foo }
foo が呼び出されると autoload -X foo により fpath からファイル foo がロードされて foo function が実態になり、実行されます

function _fzf-completion-selector() {
  setopt local_options BASH_REMATCH

  local -a tokens=(${(z)BUFFER})
  eval "fzf-preview-symbol-${(j:_:)tokens}"

  for key in ${(k)symbols}; do
    [[ "${LBUFFER/%?/}" =~ "$key" ]]
    if [[ $BASH_REMATCH[1] != "" ]]; then
      local symbol=$symbols[$key]
    else
      zle expand-or-complete
      return
    fi
    unset BASH_REMATCH
  done

  eval "fzf-preview-command-${symbol}"
}
ycino 21日 11:58:27 Slack

typeset complete_func_name="_fzf_complete_${id}"
_create_complete_func $complete_func_name  "${callback}"

  local match=""
  local max=0
  for regex in ${(k)symbols}; do
    [[ ${LBUFFER/%?/} =~ $regex ]]
    max=${#BASH_REMATCH[1]}
    candidate=$symbols[$regex]
    if [[ ${#BASH_REMATCH[1]} != "" ]] && [[ $max -ge ${#candidate} ]]; then
      match=$candidate
    fi
    unset BASH_REMATCH
  done

kuu 23日 15:21:04 Slack
ものすごく雑で汚いので参考になるかわからないけど該当部分だけ切り出して置いておきます
[[ダウンロード: 無題(Plain Text)]] 
function! s:preview_apply(text, ft) abort
  if !bufexists(b:prbuf)
    return
  endif
  call setbufvar(b:prbuf, "&ft", a:ft)
  call deletebufline(b:prbuf, 1, "$")
  call setbufline(b:prbuf, 1, a:text)
endfunction

let s:preview_job = -1
let s:preview_acc = []

function! s:preview_cb(ch, msg) abort
  call add(s:preview_acc, a:msg)
endfunction

function! s:preview_change() abort
  " Gitのメッセージ位置を取ってdiffするかファイルを直接読むかを決める
  let lines = getline(1, "$")
  let nostaged = index(lines, "Changes not staged for commit:")
  let untracked = index(lines, "Untracked files:")
  let line = getline(".")
  " Ginaはファイル部分をエスケープしてくれているので利用する
  if stridx(line, "\<Esc>") != -1
    let linepos = line(".")
    if untracked != -1 && linepos > untracked
      " untrackedより先はファイルを直接開く
      try
        " エスケープシーケンスを利用して切り出し
        let line = substitute(line, "\\v.*\<Esc>\\[\\d+m(.*)\<Esc>.*", "\\1", "")
        call s:preview_apply(readfile(line), "text")
      catch
        echo [v:exception, v:throwpoint]
        call add(g:vimrc_errors, [v:exception, v:throwpoint])
      endtry
    else
      " もうちょっと上手くできた気がするけど面倒だし当分は放置
      let line = substitute(line, "\\v[^:]*:\\s*", "", "")
      let line = substitute(line, "\\v\<Esc>.*", "", "")
      let opt = (nostaged != -1 && linepos > nostaged) ? "" : "--staged"
      silent! call job_stop(s:preview_job, "kill")
      let s:preview_acc = []
      " TODO:neovimでは動かんのでそのうちなんとかする
      let preview_job = job_start(split(printf("git diff %s %s", opt, line)), {
      \ "close_cb": {ch->s:preview_apply(s:preview_acc, "diff")},
      \ "out_cb": funcref("s:preview_cb"),
      \ })
    endif
  endif
endfunction

function! s:preview_open() abort
  execute "lcd" system("git rev-parse --show-toplevel")
  let curwin = win_getid()
  new
  let prbuf = bufnr("%")
  setlocal buftype=nofile bufhidden=hide noswapfile
  call win_gotoid(curwin)
  let b:prbuf = prbuf
  autocmd CursorMoved <buffer> call s:preview_change()
endfunction

augroup vimrc
  autocmd vimrc FileType gina-status nnoremap <buffer> pr :<C-u>call <SID>preview_open()<CR>
augroup END

MRUといえばzshrcにこんなの書いて使ってるけど案外便利
chpwd () {
  touch ~/.stack
  sed -ie "\\#^$PWD\$#d" ~/.stack
  echo $PWD >> ~/.stack
  ls -F
}

fdm () {
  cd $(tac ~/.stack | fzf +s)
}

kuu 24日 14:09:20 Slack 
#!/bin/bash
if [ $# = 0 ]; then
  SESSION=$(tmux ls -F "#{session_last_attached}	#S" | sort -nr | cut -f2 | fzf +s)
else
  SESSION=$1
fi
tmux det -s $SESSION
TERM=xterm-256color tmux a -t $SESSION

symbols+=(
  '(^git add(( -(n|p))*| --(dry-run|patch))* $)'           git_add
  '(^git branch( --(merged|remotes))? (-(m|M|d|D))? $)'    git_checkout_branch
  '(^git reset( --soft| --hard)? $)'                       git_checkout_branch
  '(^git reset -- $)'                                      git_restore_file
  '(^git diff( --color-words)? -- $)'                      git_diff_file
  '(^git diff( --cached)?( --color-words)? $)'             git_diff_branch
  '(^git checkout ([0-9a-zA-Z\_\.\/\-]* )?-- $)'           git_ls_files
  '(^git checkout( -t)? $)'                                git_checkout_branch
  '(^git revert ([0-9a-zA-Z\_\.\/\-]* )?--$) $)'           git_checkout_branch
  '(^git rebase( (-i)|(--interactive))?( --autostash)? $)' git_checkout_branch
  '(^git stash (show|pop|drop) $)'                         git_stash
  '(^git commit --fixup $)'                                git_commit
)

ycino 25日 20:22:13 Slack
ひとまずこれで・・・
function fzf-translate() {
  local out snippet key file candidate fzf_command command

  fzf_command="fzf --multi --phony --print-query --expect=ctrl-m,ctrl-q --bind=\"change:reload:echo '{q}' | nextword | tr ' ' '\n' | xargs -I WORD echo 'WORD' \" --preview='google-trans {q}'"

  IFS=$'\n' out=$(eval "echo '' | ${fzf_command}")

  while true; do
    query=$(echo "$out" | head -1)
    key=$(echo "$out" | head -2 | tail -1)
    select=$(echo "$out" | head -3 | tail -1)
    if [[ $key == "ctrl-q" ]]; then
      return
    else
      out=$(eval "echo "${query}${select}" | nextword | tr ' ' '\n' | ${fzf_command} --query='${query}${select}'")
    fi
  done
}

Turn your fzf into a live REPL
I just came up with this idea of abusing fzf --preview flag to turn simple commands into live REPL with instant feedback loop - GitHub repo Examples Live awk preview $ echo '' | fzf --print-query --preview 'echo "a\nb\nc\nd" | awk {q}' Live awk preview Peek into contents of a directory $ echo '' | fzf --preview 'ls {q}' fzf + ls Execute a Ruby script $ echo '' | fzf --print-query --preview 'ruby -e {q}' fzf + Ruby

ycino 27日 16:39:28 Slack
今の補完は candidate_command を渡すようになってるから単純な配列で補完候補を渡したりできない
ycino 27日 16:44:18 Slack
あとこれが自分の特殊な運用に乗りすぎててfzf-preview側に持っていけない
function f() {
  local project dir repository session current_session
  dir=$(ghq list -p | sed -e "s|${HOME}|~|" | fzf --prompt='Project >' --preview "glow -s dark \$(eval echo {})/README.md" --bind ctrl-d:preview-page-down,ctrl-u:preview-page-up)

  if [[ $dir == "" ]]; then
    return 1
  fi

  if [[ ! -z ${TMUX} ]]; then
    repository=${dir##*/}
    session=${repository//./-}
    current_session=$(tmux list-sessions | grep 'attached' | cut -d":" -f1)

    if [[ $current_session =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]]; then
      eval cd "${dir}"
      tmux rename-session $session
    else
      tmux list-sessions | cut -d":" -f1 | grep -e "^${session}\$" > /dev/null
      if [[ $? != 0 ]]; then
        tmux new-session -d -c $(eval echo "${dir}") -s $session
      fi
      tmux switch-client -t $session
    fi
  else
    eval cd "${dir}"
  fi
}
